        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  BMI 22-45 kg/m2;

          -  HbA1c score indicative of prediabetes (5.7-6.4%);

          -  blood pressure of <160/99 mm Hg assessed according to Canadian Hypertension Education
             Program guidelines;

          -  without diagnosed diabetes;

          -  no prior history of cardiovascular disease;

          -  not on hormone replacement therapy;

          -  Cardiovascular medications (e.g., statins) will be allowed if patients are on stable
             therapy (6 months on same dose)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  taking glucose-lowering medications;

          -  fasting triglycerides â‰¥5.5 mmol/l;

          -  any explicit contraindications to exercise (e.g., musculoskeletal injury)
